# common
1,0:\n

# help screen
2,0:Syntax (see documentation for more details background information):\n\n
2,1:Syntax (see documentation or use /Z:longhelp for more options):\n\n
# only shown if compiled with LEGACY_HELP
2,3:FORMAT drive: [/V[:label]] [/Q] [/U] [/F:size] [/B | /S] [/D]\n
2,4:FORMAT drive: [/V[:label]] [/Q] [/U] [/T:tracks /N:sectors] [/B | /S] [/D]\n
2,5:FORMAT drive: [/V[:label]] [/Q] [/U] [/4] [/B | /S] [/D]\n
2,6:FORMAT drive: [/Q] [/U] [/1] [/4] [/8] [/B | /S] [/D]\n\n
2,12: /B         Kept for compatibility, formerly reserved space for the boot files.\n
2,22: /1         Formats a single side of a floppy disk (160k / 180k).\n
2,23: /8         Formats a 5.25\" disk with 8 sectors per track (160k / 320k).\n
# only shown if compiled without LEGACY_HELP
2,7:FORMAT drive: [/V[:label]] [/Q] [/U] [/F:size] [/S] [/D]\n
2,8:FORMAT drive: [/V[:label]] [/Q] [/U] [/T:tracks /N:sectors] [/S] [/D]\n
#  /* the /4 option is a legacy shorthand for size selection: 360k in 1.2M drive */
#  /* (drive type detection and "double stepping" setting are automatic on ATs.) */
2,9:FORMAT drive: [/V[:label]] [/Q] [/U] [/4] [/S] [/D]\n\n
# shown for all
2,10: /V:label   Specifies a volume label for the disk, stores date and time of it.\n
2,11: /S         Calls SYS to make the disk bootable and to add system files.\n
2,13: /D         Be very verbose and show debugging output. For bug reports.\n
2,14: /Q         Quick formats the disk. If not combined with /U, can be UNFORMATed\n
2,15:            and preserves bad cluster marks (/Q /U does not).\n
2,16: /U         Unconditionally formats the disk. Lowlevel format if floppy disk.\n
2,17: /F:size    Specifies the size of the floppy disk to format. Normal sizes are:\n
2,18:            360, 720, 1200, 1440, or 2880 (unit: kiloBytes). /F:0 shows a list.\n
2,19: /4         Formats a 360k floppy disk in a 1.2 MB floppy drive.\n
2,20: /T:tracks  Specifies the number of tracks on a floppy disk.\n
2,21: /N:sectors Specifies the number of sectors on a floppy disk.\n

# detailed help screen
