3,4:Contributors: Jan Verhoeven, John Price, James Clark, Tom Ehlert,\n
3,5:  Bart Oldeman, Jim Hall and others. Not to forget all the testers!\n\n

3,6:Switches and additional features explained:\n
3,7:/D (debug) and /Y (skip confirmation request) are always allowed.\n
3,8:/B (reserve space for sys) is dummy and cannot be combined with /S (sys)\n
3,9:/V:label is not for 160k/320k disks. The label stores the format date/time.\n\n

3,10:Size specifications only work for floppy disks. You can use\n
3,11:either /F:size (in kilobytes, size 0 displays a list of allowed sizes)\n
3,12:or     /T:tracks /N:sectors_per_track\n
3,13:or any combination of /1 (one-sided, 160k/180k),\n
3,14:                      /8 (8 sectors per track, 160k/320k, DOS 1.x)\n
3,15:                  and /4 (format 160-360k disk in 1200k drive)\n\n

3,16:To suppress the harddisk format confirmation prompt, use    /Z:seriously\n
3,17:To save only unformat (mirror) data without formatting, use /Z:mirror\n
3,18:To UNFORMAT a disk for which fresh mirror data exists, use  /Z:unformat\n
